        "created_at": "2023-02-04T13:49:01.246Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is an existing feature request:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"25525\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/35a633/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/context-menus-for-chats/25525\">Context menus for chats</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/desktop-feature-requests/20\"><span data-category-id=\"20\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #2D8B39; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #83B72A;\" data-parent-category-id=\"17\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Desktop Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Chats have no interactivity when pressing the right mouse button onto them. \nIt would be better to have context menus, so we could: \n\nPin chat to top\nView contact / profile\nDisable notifications\nMark as unread\nDelete chat\nClear history\n\nCurrenty, some of these are accessible directly in the chat, but not as the ‚Äúright click‚Äù context menu.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
